  <div class="col-sm-6">
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h2 class="panel-title">Data Storage</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>
          ShowTime uses a web-browser feature named local storage to store your information.
          In many ways it makes your web-browser act like a desktop program.
        </p>

        <p><strong>Please be aware of the following before using:</strong></p>

        <ul>
          <li>If you clear local storage in your web-browser you will delete your <em>Show Time</em> information</li>
          <li>
            Each web-browser has its own local storage.
            This means if you run <em>Show Time</em> in Chrome, you will not see your information in FireFox, Edge, or Safari.
          </li>
          <li>If you run <em>Show Time</em> in an anonymous browser session, no data is saved when the browser window is closed.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

